@Node HINTS

How can I optimize Shapeshifter for playing games?
Ok, you want to play Doom and you have no GFX Board for a good screen refresh? No problem...
First of all, don't expect miracles if you have not AT LEAST a 68030! (Yo Djames!)
FPU and MMU are highly recommanded too!

If you're running Shapeshifter from Workbench, you must know that WB's tasks decrease Shapeshifter's performance
so I advise you to start it with a startup selector.

Many games require an high speed screen refreshment and the Shapeshifter's amiga bitplanes mode is not
a very competitive one so I recomend you tu use PD's external videodrivers wich can be easily downloaded
from Aminet.

The best external videodriver currently available is the @{"Savage" LINK Savage} package for MMU owners only!
If you haven't MMU, you can try the @{"AGA Boost" LINK AGABoost} package.
These two packages inlude some 2x2 pixelmode videodrivers, a good alternative for 3D games.

Hint: Before playing 3D games, setup the Shapeshifter'screen size to 640x480 in  LOWRES mode (refresh=4).
----- During game, setup game screen to the minimum size and use the mouse to center it.
      Warning: Some games (Doom, for an example) crashes if you attempt to scroll the screen during action.
               in order to avoid it, you MUST pause the game before center it's  screen or do it during loading
               phases (better).

About System Errors: Error code 12 could be result of a 68040 minimum configuration necessity but this  hypothesis
-------------------- must be verified...
                     Error code -108 results of an unjustified "not enough memory error".



